  "candidate_text": "Tessa runs her thumb along the fold in the program, pressing the crease sharper, as though the layout itself had made the decision and she had only read it aloud. The applause from the hall reaches her in a small, muffled pulse, and she receives it as confirmation rather than irony \u2014 the room had responded well, which meant the framing had worked, which meant the work had been served. She begins composing the reply to Eli in her head, not as an apology but as a correction of his likely misreading: donors need a single name to attach a gift to, she had given them hers because she was standing at the podium, that is how attribution works in rooms like this. The explanation is so complete and so reasonable that she holds it for a moment before noticing it has no second person in it at all.",
